D.q[4607] = "Hello, I\'m pleased you were able to find out more about Elturt. It looks as though we don\'t have much choice but to go to the Wa Castle and find the bandana. Take these 1,000 Kamas for the journey, and take a few good friends with you. The Wa Wabbit\'s well known for his love of a good fight and I don\'t think his Wobots will give up the bandana very easily.";
D.q[7432] = "";
D.q[961] = "The main aim of the militia is to protect the inhabitants of Bonta against Brakmarian attacks. We\'re also here to help you and to give information on the city. Don\'t hesitate to go visit Master Amayiro if you wish to join us. I\'ve heard he\'s looking for new spies. You\'ll find him in the fort, in the centre of the city.";
D.q[1384] = "Tinnik yik. Ikfik yik nid mik firitilliknik yik tik fitirik, dik nik hisititik ti cimik bick inik fid mik.";
D.q[2763] = "A long time ago, Pandawas often made generous libations to their goddess Pandawa.\nAt the end of the ceremonies, some Pandawas would go into a trance due to the fermented bamboo vapours... before collapsing. In a spirit of brotherhood, some followers did not hesitate to carry some of them home. That\'s the point where the history joins the legend: we don\'t really know if it was plain drunken hallucination or real evil but the intoxicated Pandawas would always fight their companions as they were being carried back home! These gesticulations and blind clouts are the origin of the Pandawa art of self-defence.";
D.q[4259] = "With this staff, I\'ll be able to carve you a particularly efficient scythe shaft. The only thing left to do is to take apart the blade of your sword.";
D.q[7965] = "So, which of these snowmonsters is the most frightening?";
D.q[6819] = "I\'ve not eaten anything yet today so I\'m just preparing some slices of Farle\'s Pig before my next game of cards with Ares Truer.";
D.q[7431] = "";
D.q[3662] = "That big stone arch over there is one. It allows you to travel from one place to another in the wink of an eye.";
D.q[334] = "Ah, it has to be the most beautiful trade in the world, after Moon Island Lighthouse Keeper, Perceptor, Confectioner, Wizard, Boowolf Tamer and Bwork Magus Taxidermist. You just have to learn to live with the weather and to flout the agricultural regulations - they want us to leave our fields fallow every second year! Imagine that. Ha!\nIt\'s a harsh trade, but perfect for lovers of nature. I\'d be glad to teach you all I know.";
D.q[4467] = "A low-ranking Bontarian militiaman carrying special equipment?\nHmm, that\'s very worrying. Could the Bontarians have found a better way to equip their soldiers?\nI see you\'ve beaten him. Excellent, that means one less to fight and it\'ll knock their confidence. You\'ve shown me that no one has the right to treat us like puppets. I\'m starting to like you.\nAs for the Whitish Fang, is it effective, at least? Oh, and I need to get it back off you, the butcher\'s offering me a lot of money for it.";
D.q[1561] = "It\'s a miracle! My Tabi is feeling better. May the gods be thrice blessed for their help!";
D.q[7966] = "";
D.q[6641] = "";
D.q[2734] = "A map? Not really... it\'s more of a reminder... To be honest, I still haven\'t had the time to draw a map of the so-called evil forest... What I\'d like to do is write a book with all the great hill-walks over there. It\'s the perfect place for tireless adventurers, you know.";
D.q[4468] = "A low-ranking Bontarian militiaman carrying special equipment?\nHmm, that\'s very worrying. Could the Bontarians have found a better way to equip their soldiers?\nI see you\'ve beaten him. Excellent, that means one less to fight and it\'ll knock their confidence. You\'ve shown me that no one has the right to treat us like puppets. I\'m starting to like you.\nAs for the Whitish Fang, is it effective, at least? Oh, and I need to get it back off you, the butcher\'s offering me a lot of money for it.";
D.q[7967] = "";
D.q[6820] = "We Ecaflips have a keen sense of smell and the overpowering stench of wildcats in here would be unbearable if we were not ourselves slightly feline. If I\'d met a Sram who smelled horrific, I\'d remember.";
D.q[6270] = "It\'s a pity I didn\'t keep it to myself. Here\'s a few Kamas so you can enjoy yourself at the Inn. Have one for me!";
D.q[1302] = "A new tax? Oto Mustam is really unscrupulous! He\'s degrading our beautiful city! I\'ll never pay this tax!";
D.q[6642] = "";
D.q[135] = "It\'s quite simple, all you need to do is buy a raffle ticket costing 10 Kamas. You might win the kitty, valued at 20,000 Kamas!";
D.q[7968] = "";
D.q[3074] = "A shark is spreading panic in the harbour. Find it and come tell me where it wreaks its sharkish terror.";
D.q[2608] = "You succeeded! Three strokes of luck in a row, I must say it\'s quite unusual! Well it\'s good for you that you\'re lucky, about the only thing you have going for you really!\nMaple Bridge, the last book I read was about the mating of the Treechnids. Males that could survive three fights against a Feca were nicknamed kokoko kukold\', fascinating isn\'t it?\n\nAlright! Faithful assistant, this time you need to go to the peninsula of the Dreggons! On the west side of the mountain, there\'s a door that looks just like the others. That\'s where your next challenge is!";
D.q[3999] = "A pint? You don\'t even deserve to be kicked around by me! Disciple! Come and teach this young ignoramus a lesson!";
D.q[7969] = "";
D.q[6643] = "";
D.q[85] = "Joining the Order is very difficult.\nHogmeiser used to be the master of the Order of the Kicked Ass, but he disappeared several years ago, leaving only his old, worn boots behind.";
D.q[7970] = "";
D.q[1581] = "It\'s not for me, I\'ve met a Grace Malcean a little further down south and she has problems with her Tabi.\nShe\'s a member of the Bontarian Parliament and it would be harmful for my electorate if she suffered from a nervous breakdown at the moment.";
D.q[5345] = "";
D.q[4437] = "A stupid old Sadida is hanging around Brakmar telling everyone we should stop praising Djaul and follow the way of our ancestors.\nI want you to eliminate him before our citizens hear his mad raving.";
D.q[2581] = "Perfect! Bring 10 Bamboos to the Shield Smith, he will be grateful";
D.q[3427] = "I.... Love.... Kids.";
D.q[7971] = "";
D.q[7780] = "Show me that, quickly. \nLet\'s see, that\'s good... It has reacted well... No trace of the virus, no mutation either... Hmmm, there remains some residue here, which may be problematic. \nListen, we\'re on the right track. Essentially, the vaccine works, but I think it\'s probably only going to be effective for a week. I can vaccinate you regularly if you bring me a sample of Mastogob blood. \nAll that\'s left is for me to find a way to extend the effects of the vaccine and, unlike the Count, the problem with the Lurgi will be just a bad memory.";
D.q[1018] = "It looks like you\'ve forgotten the beer, silly blighter. \nStart again and hurry up this time!\nYou really have to spoon-feed these awkward lumps...";
D.q[404] = "The profession of Miner is a difficult one. You must like darkness and mustn\'t be afraid of taking on Cracklers armed only with a pick.\nThis profession is nevertheless rewarding, you can become rich without too much trouble, as long as you work in the good mines.\nThe essential equipment to the miner is the pick. Take good care of it and don\'t let it get rusty.";
D.q[2058] = "A sword? You\'re here on Dragonsly\'s behalf, aren\'t you? That guy knows what he\'s talking about when it comes to steel, and life in general... Here you go, your blade is forged and sharpened. It\'s now light and fearsome.";
D.q[7972] = "Believe me, extractor and plumbing maintenance in the Tears of Ouronigride is not all fun and games. You have to keep an eye on the extractors at all times to make sure there is just the right amount of pressure, repair the faulty elements, keep the Steam Cracklers at bay and a whole load of other jobs. It\'s not what you\'d call an office job, that\'s for sure!";
D.q[4065] = "I\'m sorry, but you didn\'t prove yourself valiant enough for me to help you unlearn a spell. Defeat some more of the mythical creatures on this island and then come back and see me.";
D.q[1406] = "AHHH YES... I LOVE THE SKY-BLUE SKY! SO WHAT?! I\'m A BRAKMARIAN AFTER ALL!";
D.q[5217] = "";
D.q[5680] = "The Statuettes of Sumens? By heavens I want them! My little sister, Terra Tibya, may she rest in peace, knew where they were. She even told me where they were, but I\'ve completely forgotten. And I\'ve searched, boy oh boy, I\'ve searched high and low. I stayed with the Bworks so long that I\'ve started to look like them!\nI\'ve got an idea! Why don\'t you go ask the city\'s alchemist to make me a Remembrance Potion. Is that not a great idea?";
D.q[7433] = "";
D.q[2423] = "The fisherman\'s trade requires more patience than any other work. A fisherman basically catches fish that he cleans before selling it to fishmongers. But catching fish is not easy when you begin. You have to pay attention to when and where you go fishing...anyway you never know for sure if you\'ll come back empty-handed or not.";
D.q[7973] = "I see you\'re in agreement with me. I was doing pretty well until my imbecile of an assistant confused a natural jacuzzi with an acid bath. He died in terrible suffering and his screams of agony lasted a good hour. At least that will have taught him that appearances can be deceiving.\nGood, as you understand, I need a new assistant but I can\'t leave my post. Could you go and visit Lou Bricante, the Mayor\'s assistant, and tell her that I need a new assistant urgently if she doesn\'t want the port and the lake to freeze over again?";
D.q[1113] = "Hey wait wait wait, got some Kamas for me? No? But I can find you cheap weapons! Got some Kamas for me? I can rob people for you if you want! Got some Kamas for me? I even know how you can duplicate items! Got some Kamas for me? Got some Kamas for me? Come on, give me all your Kamas!";
D.q[5305] = "";
D.q[7974] = "Again? He asks for a new one every two months. At this rate, there won\'t be anyone who\'s skilled enough left to help him.\nI haven\'t got anyone in mind myself, but maybe our builder Valy Domidat will be able to recommend someone.";
D.q[3791] = "Hey? You wandering through these parts all on your lonesome? You might get through Incarnam with your trousers, but Amakna\'s a different ballgame, believe me. You need some friends to fall back on. Get a little book, fill it up with names... I can tell you from experience it\'s the way to go.";
D.q[6644] = "";
D.q[7975] = "I can\'t leave you Francky, he\'s too precious to me. If you really need someone, I advise you to go and speak to the head of the mines, Laurent Gebleuh. He\'s hasn\'t been up to much these last few decades and spends most of his time at the village pub. Work wouldn\'t be such a bad thing for him.";
D.q[7976] = "Who do you take me for? I give the orders, not take them.\nIf Larry Tutthe needs a new assistant, go and pester Gaston. He was one of my workers at the mine, but since they\'ve been overrun by monsters, they\'ve moved him to plumbing surveillance. It\'s more of an office job, really.\nTell him he\'s been transferred to the Tears of Ouronigride and he has no say in the matter, we\'re not a union.";
D.q[3260] = "Adventure\'s no\' in your blood, mate.\nGet ou\'... You\'re bugging me.";
D.q[940] = "Hi!\nDid you know that Bonta has an outer wall built of no less than 128.369 Crackler stones?\nDid you know that it took 250 labourers to build that wall and that about 1 in every 32 of them died in great pain during its construction?\nNo, you didn\'t! I knew you didn\'t know it!\n\nBut you can believe that they\'re using part of the city\'s budget, #1 Kamas to be exact, to pay their widows\' pensions?\n\nOf course you can\'t believe it. But I said it, so it must be so. Now, go away, I\'m busy.";
D.q[3362] = "Modifications brought by the update are listed on the official forums, in the Logbook section.";
D.q[6645] = "";
D.q[7977] = "Don\'t disturb me, I have to watch over the plumbing. If there\'s an accident while I\'m talking to you, they\'ll say it\'s my fault and they\'ll transfer me to Alma\'s Cradle. I don\'t want to spend the next ten years in the company of ghosts.";
D.q[5721] = "Before I put you to the test, I have some bad news for you. Dike Tarak, Amayiro\'s nephew, was kidnapped last night while camping in the Cania Plains with some other children and supervised by several militiamen. Niamuh Boulkier was one of them.\nYou must go and see him and find out what happened, and if at all possible, it would be a great relief if you could bring Dike Tarak back to us.";
D.q[3657] = "Here is a recipe that I need you to take to my client, Babblera. She\'ll pay you when she gets it.";
D.q[3406] = "The road is not the destination, young one, but the road is... the road is long... the end of the road is the destination. Usually. Take a turnip for instance. It\'s round, a never-ending spiral could be walked upon its surface... but it only has one... stalk. The stalk is where you must go, young one... search for the stalk and you\'ll eat the turnip of your destiny. Is that what you seek, child?";
D.q[7978] = "Hot baths all year round, no more frostbite, no more Lurgi, what more could you ask for?";
D.q[7979] = "He strikes me as being a bit of a weakling. I hope he\'s not one of those hopeless office workers.\nBy the way, while you were wandering around the village, I got an urgent call to help with this extractor. As you can see, it\'s being repaired at the moment but it\'s going to take a while. Take Gaston with you and go and check on the other extractors to make sure there are no problems.\nEven if you don\'t find anything wrong, come back and see me to let me know.";
D.q[6646] = "";
D.q[3883] = "Haha! Flattery ... nice try! Alright, wretch, I\'ll go talk to your boss. Give me back your Rogue emblem, you still don\'t deserve it...";
D.q[4127] = "There we go! Everything\'s ready for your departure! \nWe can leave whenever you want. But be careful, it\'s a dangerous trip and I suggest you leave with a couple of friends who are stronger than you, or else I\'m not sure you\'ll survive the trip. Indeed, a single perverted seagull could kill you with a couple of pecks.";
D.q[7980] = "What type of damage?\nOk, I see. Gaston\'s going to keep an eye on the damaged extractor while you go and get a crate of materials from Valy Domidat.\nDon\'t worry about a list, she\'s used to it and will know what I need. She\'s a hell of a woman!";
D.q[7545] = "Here below lies Jorbak the Venal. Only those rich enough in Kamas to attract his lust may enter. Eleven Kamas for every year that he lived before losing his fortune, plus six Kamas because that was all he had left.";
D.q[2549] = "He added: Tell him he can\'t decline this honow considewing what we know about him...";
D.q[6647] = "";
D.q[548] = "Over here, sailor *hic* it\'s a graaave moment *hic*! No mooore driiink *hic* to fill up this hooold *hic*...\nBut that\'s not the wooooorst *hic* my Muuse has disappeaaaared *hic* my Greaaat Wooden Skeleton *hic* my moodel when I had nothing better to do...*hic*";
D.q[1243] = "Hem, this recipe must come from the storehouses of Bonta... I really wonder how it wound up in your hands.\nAnyway, I need 3 measures of Magic cure and 1 measure of Elbow grease. I also need you to lend me a Flint so I can finish the recipe.";
D.q[7981] = "Francky, give me a hand.\nSo...he\'ll need that tool, and that one too... Two boxes...\nIt\'s ready. Larry Tutthe should be able to deal with anything once he\'s got this.";
D.q[7662] = "It\'s so cold here...";
D.q[3724] = "Piwi piwi piwi?";
D.q[1544] = "H\'m, I see dreadful creatures...I see strange and exotic places...I see you, you\'re fighting humongous monsters...you have the strength of ten and your senses are perfect... keep fighting like this and you\'ll soon be a great warrior #1!";
D.q[4475] = "Ah! In a cave in the Porcos\' Territory.\nParanoid is he? It won\'t be easy negotiating with him then, especially if he ever finds out who we are. All the same, we have to try. And if it comes to it, there\'s always plan Z...";
D.q[2412] = "Hi, are you looking for some work? If you are, you\'ve come to the right place. I can give you some information about different jobs and tell you where you might find a potential master.";
D.q[1248] = "Hmmmm, he wants me to replace him at the North Gate? Well, I\'ll go after my break at the Burnt Cat.\nPfff, thanks... NOT.";
D.q[7982] = "Show me that.\nLet\'s see, she thought of that, two boxes of that, the tools to do that. I think it\'s all there.\nThanks, you\'ve done well.";
D.q[6648] = "";
D.q[2216] = "By Bauxite, iron and Manganese, thank you! Without you, \'would have been this big rat\'s dinner! \'Never seen anything that big on legs! \'Were on patrol in the underpass when beasties attacked. \'Stayed here, stuck by the monster. Must be fights still going on but with the echoes, \'can\'t tell where it\'s happening... For a pick\'s sake, what\'s going on in Astrub?";
D.q[2241] = "Old friend! Look at this metal ore...\n*takes out a shapeless stone which looks a lot like iron ore*\nIt\'s worth a fortune, don\'t you think?";
D.q[2400] = "Mining is a vocation, it takes a lot of time but it\'s worth it in the end. At the beginning, of course, you only find pig iron or shiny pebbles... It\'s a matter of intuition. But once you have some experience, you\'ll find your gold, don\'t you worry!";
D.q[3166] = "Ah! You look lost again! How can I help you?";
D.q[1021] = "Hem, in the end I\'m too swamped with work to take care of my sabre myself.\nGo to the Blacksmiths district and ask Kosuke to repair my blade.";
D.q[3087] = "Ah, I just love a neat and tidy exchange. I\'m going to call to my old friend Wartella and have a nice, cold Pig Milk. Thanks to her, I know I can trust you.";
D.q[2842] = "Do you wish to come back? I\'ll take you to the Zaap in the village and from there you can go to the central Zaap.";
D.q[1233] = "Hem I see, that\'s just like Mustam, each time someone makes his head spin, he sends him to me. Last time it was Lothar Murofud, what an impatient character!\nCan I ask you a favour? Tell Tink Berval to come replace me. I\'m fed up with keeping watch on that door!";
D.q[7569] = "Ah, I see you don\'t mess about! You\'re ready to explore the vast continent of Amakna, and then some.";
D.q[2449] = "Hello, brave adventurer. Welcome to our humble home. We are a clan of noble mercenaries, devoted to the people. We take care of all sorts of things. For a few Kamas, we\'ll help you find that item you\'ve been looking for, we\'ll accompany you in your dangerous adventures... you want someone killed? We can do that too... Please come inside if you want to meet our clan. You can join us if you like, just contact the clan master.";
D.q[1238] = "What a beautiful day, huh?";
D.q[7983] = "Since you\'re offering... I need some help to take some samples and transport them to the village. I\'m renting part of Ernest Laye\'s warehouse to store the bottles and carry out the research, so if you have time, you need to take the samples from here and drop them off there. Make sure you don\'t disturb the pond\'s tenants.";
D.q[6583] = "Ah, him. It\'s actually the first time I\'ve seen him. He wanted to know if I worked for Bonta but I told him no. I told him that Nara worked for them though... should I have?";
D.q[7984] = "Strange, that doesn\'t look like anything I\'ve ever seen before. Look, I\'m not a naturalist. You would be better off showing it to an alchemist. It\'s more his field of expertise than mine. But, before you go, please take these samples to Ernest Laye.";
D.q[1445] = "Ah, I want to fight! I really want to fight! But I\'m the strongest so nobody wants to fight with me! Everybody is afraid of me! Ahah! Hey you! Do you want to fight or are you just gonna grovel like the others?";
D.q[6651] = "";
D.q[2804] = "Oh, I see... exceptional circumstances, I\'ll take you directly to the Master and will bring you back out straight after your interview.";
D.q[4539] = "Ah, it\'s you! Can we begin the attack? The Brakmarian patrol is going to arrive any minute now.";
D.q[7985] = "Just put them in the corner, there. I\'ll put them away later.";
D.q[5688] = "...";
D.q[4806] = "Ah, it\'s you *hic*. I need your help with something. I am handling the trial of the accused traitor Kit Dingaround, but I\'ve *hic* broken my wooden hammer. I need a new one for the courtroom, but not just any old hammer. I need a *hic* Scraping Hammer. I\'m *hic* counting on you.";
D.q[5267] = "Ah, it\'s a good thing you came when you did. While the other soldiers take on the bulk of the troops, we\'ll attack Ronan the Barbarian. Goblins are cowardly and not too smart. If I manage to pick them off, victory is ours. You can go and distract the guards.";
D.q[4442] = "Ah, perfect. I\'ll have to avoid losing so many spies this time. The day before yesterday they mixed up a jar of poison with our stealth cream... it wasn\'t pretty. It\'s difficult to hide here as there are so many Bontarians about, so we want to you find us somewhere to lay low for a while. Try and find a location between here and the library, just so we won\'t have the whole of Bonta passing by. Actually, why don\'t you just find someone else\'s hideout and knock everyone in there out. Make sure you don\'t kill them though, we need some human guinea pigs to test the poison on. Bring 10 Flax Strings to tie them up.";
D.q[2224] = "Ah, thanks for the cake! And take this, it\'s for the delivery.";
D.q[7986] = "It\'s so adorable! Where did you find it? In the Tears of Ouronigride?!\nI\'m no expert on animals. You should take it to a different alchemist, but I doubt you\'ll find the one you need on Frigost Island. You would be better looking elsewhere. It will save you time.";
D.q[6652] = "";
D.q[7663] = "Meeeeeoooooww!";
D.q[2505] = "Long live Pandala!";
D.q[7987] = "That looks interesting, but I haven\'t got time to look into it now.\nGo and see my assistant Kimiya in the underground laboratory at the Coral Beach. He will be delighted to examine this creature.";
D.q[6567] = "Ah, that I like better. I don\'t trust people who do too much, they\'re always hiding something... At least you didn\'t let me walk all over you, that means you\'re not too eager to get me. I\'ll definitely think about your offer.";
D.q[5727] = "Long live Brakmar... I look such an idiot, always screaming the same bloody thing.";
D.q[4925] = "The forging of the Dawn Shard, the weapon used by the Wise Jiva, requires exotic materials.\nAs you probably know, Jiva is the symbol of loyalty to the gods, particularly towards Xelor, and so it is logical that the Dawn Shard\'s powers reflect the mastery of time. This is why we must steal a fragment of time.\nThe problem is, to steal time, one must have access to Xelor\'s Clock. But no one has access except the Demons of the Hours, who to my knowledge are best placed to do this mischief. Once again, it will be necessary to contact one of them.\nAccording to some of my contacts, recent rumours say that the Rogues are dealing with the Demons of the Hours. Although they are merely rumours, it\'s the only lead available to us. You must make your way to their hideout and haggle with them until you get a stolen Fragment of Time.";
D.q[5316] = "";
D.q[6653] = "";
D.q[7988] = "I\'ve never seen anything like it. The creature\'s growth seems to be frozen.\nI should be able to fix that, but I need some ingredients for my potions.\nI\'m going to keep the creature under observation while you go and get me 10 Snailmet Slobber and 1 Tynril Pistil. Oh, and I also need some things from the area where you found him and, from what I\'ve heard, there might be some steam-filled eggs. I\'ll need about 10 of them.";
D.q[6423] = "You\'re like a bad smell, you are. Show me your sword.\n...\nI\'ve seen many Ecaflips with this type of sword. The ones who live outside the city walls. I can\'t remember where exactly though - do you think I remember everywhere I go, do you? Speaking of going, didn\'t I ask you to get the hell out of here? How about I give you a makeover with my fingernails?";
D.q[1449] = "Ah, well done! Very good, let\'s move on to more serious matters... Hem, a moron set fire to the firewood stock of the militia. If you don\'t want to sleep in the cooler, go and get 10 Treechnid barks and bring them back here. Don\'t forget... I need 10... Take this reminder, since you\'re so absent-minded.";
D.q[6655] = "";
D.q[7989] = "Everything\'s ready. All I need now are the things you\'ve brought me.\nI just need to add that, then mix, cover the strange creature with it... and it\'s worked!\nIts growth has restarted at an accelerated rate. Hurry up and get this creature back where you found it if you want it to reach maturity without suffering any side effects.";
D.q[1273] = "Leave me alone!";
D.q[6656] = "";
D.q[7990] = "Thank you for saving me. The demon left me here encased in lava, but the big freeze prevented my growth. Now I\'m an adult and free from my acts, I\'m going to find a way to show you my gratitude.";
D.q[398] = "Hey, I\'m Eowine Fiole, a great potion specialist. It\'s your lucky day...I need some ingredients. \nHelp me find them and you\'ll be generously rewarded.";
D.q[1180] = "Hi, hi, hi! What would you like? Chicken, beef, pork?\nOur menu will excite the most refined of tastes. Our wish is your comm... sorry. Your wish is... our command.";
D.q[4525] = "Ah, you\'re back. Danathor wanted to see you again. You\'re starting to make a name for yourself round these parts... everyone wants to hire you!";
D.q[93] = "Hey, I need something to ease this pain, a Boowolf yanked out my moustache in a fight and it\'s killing me, so if you have any bread to spare, I\'ll take it off your hands. \nI bet you\'ve never met Wiss Catz, have you?";
D.q[6657] = "";
D.q[7991] = "Before you go, take these coins. I found them at the bottom of the pond. They\'re of no use to me but I\'ve seen that you already have some, so you must use them for something.";
D.q[7664] = "If I\'m not mistaken, Grace is in the Militia at the moment. She\'s a lovely person, but sometimes her responsibilities as council member force her to make some difficult decisions.";
D.q[3030] = "Hola amigo! Life is only worth living when you\'re on a battlefield, isn\'t it true? Virile trainings and moonlight patrols, are what you really want to do? And I haven\'t mentioned the loyal friendship between the militia of Bonta yet! So are you in?";
D.q[3775] = "Do you wish to return to your statue, young one?";
D.q[7992] = "I knew the journey to the village would be risky, but I didn\'t expect to be attacked by so many monsters on the way back.\nPlease help us.";
D.q[4838] = "Ah, you\'re back. Did everything go as planned?";
D.q[4945] = "Ah, you\'re back. I just received a troubling report. Troops from Brakmar led be Oto Mustam himself were seen coming from Amakna. I sent a group of elite troops there and I want you to join them under the command of officer Imagiro. The soldiers have set up camp near the Iop temple. I\'ve marked it out on your map for you.";
D.q[6096] = "Ah, you\'re back. I presume that your presence means the Assembly is over?";
D.q[315] = "Stop laughing and go find me 10 Moskito Wings. I must come up with a brilliant idea and I\'m short of Moskito Wings, they help me think. \nYou obviously don\'t deserve it but I\'ll find a way to reward you.";
D.q[7993] = "I think our cawottes are cooked.";
D.q[4283] = "It\'s you! You\'ll never guess what happened to me.";
D.q[1572] = "Oh, I almost lost my shop but Danathor, a loyal regular, totally disagreed with Amayiro. He\'s going to try to vote in a law to legalize Tofu fighting.";
D.q[7341] = "";
D.q[7342] = "";
D.q[1330] = "HYYAAAAH, By Jiva, the poor Wabbits! YOU\'RE A BRUTE, GET OUT!";
D.q[3363] = "Huh? You made it? You really made it?\nErr... So... I didn\'t think you have them... blablablabla.... Twelve billion used Bwork protections... that\'s not it... Ah! Here... Bring the six Dofus. So... I must give you...\n...\n\nHummm. Are you ready for your reward?";
D.q[7994] = "When I think of all that trouble we went through to get supplies to the inhabitants of the sunken village... Anyone would think the Gods are against us.";
D.q[5017] = "";
D.q[5734] = "...";
D.q[7343] = "";
D.q[6475] = "I understand, you must feel terrible. No more beautiful evenings under the stars on the Cania Plains. No one to keep you company through the long nights. No one to lick your face in the morning.\nThe loss of a pet is always hard to take but I\'ve heard that there\'s a way to bring a ghost pet to life. You should find a Cemetery in the swamp and overcome all the challenges you encounter there.";
D.q[2680] = "Ahahahaha! That\'s no news to a Pandawa!";
D.q[2841] = "Someone from the Order of the Sharp Eye has brought us the hides of three Bontarian renegades. We need to study them, but the usual methods of resurrection don\'t seem to work. \nBring me a work entitled \'Erzal\'s Blessing\' from the library.";
D.q[7995] = "I thought once we\'d reached the village, we\'d be over the worst. I was wrong.";
D.q[6479] = "Ah, it\'s you. Come closer, I won\'t bite. Amayiro asked me to pass a message on to you. He would have come himself, but he\'s afraid of being followed.";
D.q[5168] = "";
D.q[3917] = "Ahem, I dunno know what my uncle\'s up to this time. My nurse came to the castle and took my measurements for a dress. How Weird is that! I\'ve been wearing the same stupid thing for ages and now everyone wants to make me a new dress!";
D.q[7996] = "If we get out of this alive, I swear I\'ll never set foot here again.";
D.q[5020] = "";
D.q[7344] = "";
D.q[4178] = "I\'m Crocodyl Dandy. I sew naughty underwear from Crocodyl scales, hypnotise plain boars with my fingers, and have a burning desire to turn this island into a Theme Park!\nI\'m sure that adventurers who crave new experiences will enjoy this island, though it\'s filled with all these dangerous creatures. Modern adventurers like to be thrilled but not to take risks. Unfortunately, since the creatures escaped from their cages and now evolve freely in the wild, I had to give up my theme park idea. Now, I must come up with something new.";
D.q[7997] = "Grrrr.";
D.q[1531] = "Oh, it\'s a quiet area, bakers do their job scrupulously and the inhabitants regularly come see me.\nHum... and at night there\'s a bit of hustle and bustle in the North what with Ufot\'s place being there.";
D.q[2624] = "Argh! How did you know I was not a real Pandawa?!";
D.q[3521] = "Me first goblinmagus!";
D.q[6822] = "I have other fish to fry. Why don\'t you look for someone else to bother with your questions?";
D.q[4209] = "Ahem, according to your constitution, I can tell that I\'ll need a Great Coralator relic to prepare your potion. Once ground to powder, I\'ll be able to withdraw all the magic power I need from it.";
D.q[7998] = "Because of your weakness, my friends have been massacred. I have nothing more to say to you.";
D.q[4114] = "Stop. \nWho would cross the Bridge of Death must answer me these questions mine, or tonight in hell will dine.";
D.q[5271] = "";
D.q[1116] = "Meeeooow.... FFFfffffffffffffff!";
D.q[7345] = "";
D.q[4356] = "Ecaflips? I definitely haven\'t seen any since they\'re all barred from my tavern... every last one. Well... most of them anyway. They spend their time annoying the customers and fighting over their stupid games.";
D.q[7999] = "You have succeeded, you\'ve saved us all! We\'re going to make it home. Take these Kamas. It\'s not much, but it\'s all we have. If you ever go back to the village, please don\'t mention this to our Mayor. Contact with the pariahs of the sunken village is forbidden and we might get sent to prison if she finds out.";
D.q[1850] = "Meow!";
D.q[2640] = "Lanma free?";
D.q[8000] = "So, despite the strict ban on travelling there, the inhabitants of the town pitted themselves against the outcasts of the sunken village. I will take the necessary measures to punish those law-breakers.\nHere is your reward for your loyalty.";
D.q[5564] = "I\'ve just got here. I haven\'t cast the spell yet. If the potion is contaminated, I\'d rather you have it. Take it.";
D.q[4087] = "Ahem, according to your constitution, I can tell that I\'ll need a Great Coralator relic, a Gourlo the Terrible relic, a Greater Bherb relic and a Tynril relic to prepare your potion. Once ground to powder, I\'ll be able to withdraw all the magic power I need from them.";
D.q[8001] = "Have you got something to say? No, really nothing?\nI have the impression that you\'re hiding something.\nYou really have nothing to say?";
D.q[665] = "I\'m Hel Munster. Many people associate my name with the best wizardry in Amakna. But I\'m just a humble searcher through the annals of magic and anything connected to it. As for research, I\'ve never been that busy...";
D.q[5730] = "...";
D.q[6430] = "Ecaflips? Dozens of voyagers pass through this gate every day, and that\'s just when it\'s quiet. During fairs, festivals and pilgrimages, I see hundreds of faces!";
D.q[7138] = "";
D.q[6982] = "Hmmmm. Wyrmwell. That rings a bell. Oh, yes, I remember! Farmhand Ruprecht, an expert in dragon lore, told me about it during an orgy. It\'s him you need to ask, he settled in the breeder village, among the Koalaks. That reminds me, he still owes me ten lashes.";
D.q[8002] = "The older I get, the more paranoid I become.\nI have had very positive feedback about your actions from the people of Frigost and I want to thank you by offering you these few Kamas.\nIf you see something unusual, please let me know. If the information is worth rewarding, I shall be generous.";
D.q[4226] = "I\'m Kroula, prophet of a fearsome monster... What is hiding behind this door scuppered any hopes of your returning home. Mayhem as he wakens at dawn, the terrible sound of the King of the island, the King of the World!";
D.q[4951] = "Ahh, little cockroach. I have some big plans I need your help with. I can\'t move like I could before with these cursed shackles on my feet. I need you to cooperate with me and to work efficiency on any tasks I give you.";
D.q[6987] = "Dardondakal the Wise was one of the three white dragons. Due to his nature, he was fairly close to the city of Bonta. The black dragons were suspected of having murdered him in the year 128, and it was for this reason that the white dragon Croulaklakoss flew to Bonta\'s rescue when the city was besieged by hordes of crocodyls led by Crocoburio. Indeed, the black dragon Grougalorasalar, Crocoburio\'s father, often trailed in the wake of his son, and Croulaklakoss jumped at the chance to avenge the death of his brother. The fight was rough but ended with the death of Grougalorasalar, which also put an end to the massacres perpetrated by Crocoburio, who was killed by the Bontarians.";
D.q[4376] = "Ah, I see our proposition interests you. The deal is simple: the jewel for 10,000 Kamas. And your life. I\'ll give you a fake jewel that you can then give to your idiot chief. So?";
D.q[1890] = "Take these scissors - make sure you equip them and not a weapon or else you\'ll damage the flower. Go and hunt the demonic rose north-west of here, you\'ll find some in the fields near the farm.";
D.q[3283] = "I\'m not joking! You should have seen it with your very eyes to realize how impressive it was! \nI took advantage of this situation and used my boat as a bridge and I made tourists pay to go to Moon Island without having to use this stupid cannon!\nI became so rich after that that I put up the money for the construction of the bridge to Pandala and the reconstruction of Bonta\'s great wall, just for fun!\nLater, my boat disappeared, sucked up at the bottom of the Asse Sea, by the Giant Kralove from Moon Island.";
D.q[7137] = "";
D.q[8003] = "I\'m cold, so cold....";
D.q[8004] = "My soul has been trapped in this world of ice for nearly a century now because of a rival\'s jealousy.\nI was murdered by Jean-Louis, a farmer who coveted my fields, a few seconds before the big freeze. He didn\'t miss me.\nInstead of reincarnating, my soul was trapped when the curse of eternal winter hit Frigost.\nI tried everything, but there is no way to free myself. However, revenge is always possible because it is a dish best served cold but before that, I have another favour to ask. Will you help me?";
D.q[4291] = "I think you can guess what your next job will be. Go to the Drunken Pandawa Inn between 4 pm and midnight, meet Xephires and speak to him about our proposition. A big sac of Kamas is waiting for him if he plays along.";
D.q[7140] = "";
D.q[5787] = "";
D.q[6836] = "Really? We don\'t have a moment to lose. Ask Ture Inge how far he\'s got with Gnirreh and ask him if he needs your help. I\'ll do my best to delay the trial. I\'ve just got a new recruit who is doing cleaning chores, they will be delighted to learn that they have more time to clean the court.";
D.q[8005] = "I don\'t know how my wife Ghislaine is. Go and visit her and tell her what happened. She lives in a small house in the port, to the north-west.";
D.q[4361] = "Ahh, yes, I think I remember. Lodax.";
D.q[1939] = "Ahhh! Finally a bit of action! Ahahaha! Tell your master we\'ll take care of it! I got a pile of fresh new recruits itching to get some battle scars they can show off! We will need some back-up though... How about we ask the Eniripsa and Feca clans to help us out?";
D.q[3152] = "It\'s a fascinating profession, but maybe a bit too difficult for a little girl like me.\nHa! I\'m kidding! We work together with breeders to invent various machines to take care of the mounts, so their owners are free to wander round the town or just sit still for days on end on their porches - a popular pastime round these parts. But mounts are quite violent when handled by heavy machinery, so our inventions always end up getting worn out before long. It\'s great for business!!!";
D.q[5277] = "";
D.q[6993] = "Merlin is correct, I\'m a specialist in astral projection and the separation of body and mind. That said, I do not know how to find and capture a lost thought, because my powers are limited to the present, not the past. However, I remember having heard about flutterthoughts in the breeder village, during a trip to the Koalak Mountains. You should go there and talk to its inhabitants, with a little luck you\'ll find someone who could tell you more about them.";
D.q[2231] = "Ahhh, my cake! Nothing\'s better than a sugary treat when I\'m forging swords. I\'m telling you, you have good timing!";
D.q[8006] = "This is a very complex maze, so listen very carefully to what I tell you!\nYou\'re at the entrance. By entering to your right, you\'ll have access to the first 25 rooms of the maze, which form a large square. I\'ve even made a drawing on the table next to me!\nUse one of the levers in the room you\'re in to trigger the doors of the facing room. The doors in the same line will close, but the others will open.\nBe careful though, and keep in mind that you can\'t open the doors of the room you\'re in yourself. Other adventurers will need to open a path for you. Simple, right?";
D.q[4517] = "Ahhh, don\'t come near me!";
D.q[1086] = "Take your new blade! What do you mean \'That was quick[\'? It\'s not for nothing I\'m the most renowned Blade Smith of Bonta...";
D.q[8007] = "So, are you already lost? Hahaha, I thought so when I saw you arrive, I knew you wouldn\'t be able to find your way through this maze of rooms. Fortunately, if you like, I can help you return to the entrance.";
D.q[4005] = "Not enough!";
D.q[460] = "Ahoy matey! Fancy a little trip? While I was sailing round the world in 80 days, I discovered, a really pleasant island, inhabited by strange creatures. We put some of them on a spit, and I can tell you their meat is absolutely delicious. If you\'re interested in a little gastronomic voyage, I can give you a return ticket for 500 Kamas.";
D.q[7141] = "";
D.q[5709] = "";
D.q[6669] = "";
D.q[8008] = "I get the impression that you don\'t really understand. If it helps at all, the rooms are numbered from left to right, which will help you identify where you are and organise things with your teammates. Oh, that reminds me... I forgot to warn you, you\'ve got no chance if you go alone! The more people there are in your group, the more likely you are make it through this terrible maze.\nOnce inside, you\'ll see that I\'ve hung a coloured flag on each door to make things easier for you. I\'ve even removed the bars blocking the first room!";
D.q[6262] = "Aie! It\'s Oto Mustam! He ordered the delay of the transfer just in case Bonta tried something stupid. He wasn\'t wrong.";
D.q[4371] = "Aie. You didn\'t manage to protect the convoy, that bothers me a lot. The bandits will now feel untouchable and their attacks will become more daring. All the same, we\'re not giving up hope just yet.";
D.q[666] = "I\'ll only teach you the basics of how to make magic equipment under the following conditions:\n- First, you must master the making of standard equipment.\n- Then, you must prove to me that you deserve my teaching.";
D.q[6671] = "";
D.q[5632] = "I believe that Xelor gives too many powers to his disciples and that Fecas are just useless, even though no one in Amakna dares to tell them so.";
D.q[4373] = "I had a meeting with some of my superiors and although we didn\'t all agree from the outset, we finally decided to set a trap for the bandits. A priceless jewel will be transported to Astrub, but I\'ll make sure a few elite militiamen will be expecting the robbers.";
D.q[6672] = "";
D.q[1094] = "Blow it, you don\'t trust me? Take it but don\'t forget to give it back.";
D.q[4066] = "I discovered this island several years ago - I have to admit that luck played a part. I was looking for a kind of new Eden, an island untouched by all the perversions that plague the continent... \nI arrived by chance - I was shipwrecked here while searching for another island. In fact, luck couldn\'t have been kinder to me, this island is just perfect.";
D.q[5320] = "";
D.q[5529] = "All the best for your new life in Amakna.";
D.q[8009] = "What are you doing here? Did Seb Atier send you or something?";
D.q[4768] = "All your nightmares have come true little one. Oto will be pleased with the power of this blade.";
D.q[6673] = "";
D.q[6674] = "";
D.q[430] = "I\'ve several missions for you. But for some of them I need warriors of trust who have proven their devotion to the Rogues.\nYou may specialise in several fields, such as robbery or assassination, but we also need couriers to deliver messages to the different evil masters of the region.";
D.q[1772] = "I\'ve trained some Dopples to fight like Ecaflips. They make good training adversaries no matter what your level is.";
D.q[8010] = "You look lost already, when it\'s so easy! Yet another clueless tourist! \nLook, if there\'s one thing you need to remember, it\'s that I can take you back to your starting point whenever you feel trapped or are just simply lost. \nNow go, I have nothing else to teach you.";
D.q[6676] = "";
D.q[6675] = "";
D.q[2697] = "Hum, well a fake Dofus... but it\'s been sculpted into precious ore by a handy little Enutrofette... Trust me!";
D.q[4484] = "I\'ve another mission for you. I recently received a letter from Xephires. We did well to get him on our side... there\'s a Bontarian ship called The Panta Maria that\'s going to be filled to bursting with all sorts of magical objects. They\'re on their way to the Port of Madstredam for unloading and you\'re the one who\'s going to relieve them of their precious cargo before any more ships come to escort them. First of all you should question Lily their captain to see if the ship has already arrived. And I don\'t need to tell you that if you fail, you\'ll be tortured the Tofoone way.";
D.q[8011] = "Do you realise what you\'re saying?\nYou claim that Jean-Louis murdered my husband Robert, when in fact they were childhood friends. In addition, you have the audacity to say that it was Robert, who has been dead for nearly a century, who told you, and you want me to believe you?\nIf you have no proof to back up your claim, I would ask you to leave, immediately.";
D.q[5301] = "";
D.q[5711] = "";
D.q[5774] = "Hello there, I\'m Gobwalina, one of the most famous Gobbowl players in Amakna. I\'ve even trained King Allister\'s official team. Would you like me to give you a tour of our Gobbowl field?";
D.q[753] = "I\'ve an investigation for you: try to find information on AncestralZ. He\'s a masked pseudo-dispenser of justice who pretends to lay down the law, but I\'m the law!\nTalk to every inhabitants of Bonta and find the rotter.\n\n(One of them is lying and the others protect him, your goal is to find the good one.)";
D.q[737] = "I put in a word for you with Danathor, the steward of Bonta, some time ago and he\'d like to meet you. Why? I don\'t know, he may ask you a favour or offer you a present...";
D.q[5278] = "";
D.q[2542] = "I said, \'first bring a Pandapiler to the master of Akwadala!\'";
D.q[8012] = "I\'ve got an idea. Tell her that during our honeymoon, isn\'t wasn\'t the dog who had gastric flu. Nobody other than us knows that story, it should convince her that you\'re not lying.";
D.q[4464] = "I\'ve received a troubling report. Some of our warriors were defeated and left for dead on the way to Astrub. Whoever did it\'s still hanging around there as we speak.\nI want you to go investigate... and find the culprit!";
D.q[2154] = "Oh, a visitow in my fowest, you awe vewy bwave to ventuwe hewe.";
D.q[169] = "I need Ash Wood to keep the tavern\'s fire lit but I don\'t have time to go get any myself. If you bring me one unit, I\'ll give you some water in return.";
D.q[6679] = "";
D.q[2805] = "You\'re in the Village of Terrdala. But only those who have recently proven their strength can enter.";
D.q[5646] = "I\'ve followed your journey, Knife Fighter. You\'re evolving, but you\'re not evolving quickly enough. If you wish to rise through the ranks of our Order, you\'ll have to buy some socks and pull them up.";
D.q[1619] = "I\'m afraid of heights, though it might seem strange for a citizen of this village. I\'ve been suffering from vertigo since my childhood. To calm me down, my mother used to give me jelly sweets... ohh that calmed me down alright.";
D.q[8013] = "How did you know about that?\nWhat you have told me is very troubling, I need to think. Let\'s meet tonight after 7pm to the south of the western exit, near the wall at the boundary between the town and the harbour. I will have made my decision on what to do avenge my late husband.";
D.q[4936] = "";
D.q[6680] = "";
D.q[5054] = "So the Amakneans want to deal with Amayiro directly, do they? Whatever the case, Ebru of El took the advice to withdraw troops from Amakna, so the affair is sorted out for the moment. \nThanks for telling me. I won\'t forget the gesture.";
D.q[2861] = "I\'ve nothing to teach you at the moment. Come back later.";
D.q[7845] = "I wouldn\'t say no. We have a lot of problems with the drills and fishing lines, they deteriorate much faster than we can repair them.\nIf you feel up to it, I need 5 Aspen wood to repair the drills. I also need 50 Mastogob wool, 30 Venerable Mastogob Wool and 5 Royal Mastogob Wool to make rope and repair the fishing lines, plus 5 Glacial Boar Tusks and 5 Sabredon teeth for hooks.\nFor information, our rigs\' boilers operate on Pingwin blubber, and not wood. Trees are too rare to be wasted, however, Pingwins are numerous enough to be killed without remorse. So bring me 100 Pingwin Blubber to use as fuel.";
D.q[556] = "Alright, for the modest sum of 200 Kamas, I can give you a one-way trip to paradise, and this time the agency guarantees it will be 100% secure - satisfaction or your money back.";
D.q[8014] = "You\'re still alive? They told me that...";
D.q[5239] = "";
D.q[1309] = "Ha-ha-ha, what a bunch of idiots! Well, you\'re very efficient, I must say!";
D.q[6683] = "";
D.q[3353] = "You want to shear the Royal Gobball\'s wool off, don\'t you? Well, you either need to find the key to his den in the entrails of one of his fellow creatures, or to bring me everything that\'s on this list! Your choice! Both are difficult...";
D.q[493] = "I have no letter to send him right now.";
D.q[5007] = "";
D.q[5716] = "";
D.q[6684] = "";
D.q[1375] = "I haven\'t got all the samples I need for my research so I can\'t write a thorough report.";
D.q[6686] = "";
D.q[1235] = "Only nine pods? The militia is really squeamish, if we want to exterminate Brakmar one day, there\'ll have to be one heck of a row!\nAnyway, since you\'ve been sent by the militia, you have a 50% discount, so that makes 18,000 Kamas...";
D.q[6742] = "I haven\'t seen anything out of the ordinary for the moment, but I\'ll keep my eye open.";
D.q[6687] = "";
D.q[8016] = "I can give you the remains of Robert\'s fortune, which represents about 20,000 Kamas. What do you think?";
D.q[6685] = "";
D.q[5919] = "An evil little crow? Isn\'t that original. I don\'t know which to pick out of all these. Come and see me when you know which one you want to get rid of.";
D.q[8017] = "I\'ll go and fetch you it...\nNow take the money and leave.";
D.q[687] = "And here is the second question,\nHow can you measure the attention\nWithin a couple of lovers.\nIn terms of quantity, it will be better.";
D.q[5717] = "I spoke about you to various Order masters and they\'re prepared to accept you into their ranks. You\'ll have to go to the Bontarian Tower of Orders where they\'ll help you choose a path.\nThere\'s no rush, you\'ve all the time in the world to choose an Order, and you won\'t be roped into anything.";
D.q[3862] = "Hello!";
D.q[5021] = "An order slip for a A 638 Dwarf Bus! Thank Danathor for me.";
D.q[6689] = "";
D.q[8018] = "What a strange little tale. I will conduct my own investigation, thank you for letting me know.";
D.q[6690] = "";
D.q[648] = "I\'ve had the Forgetfulness recipe for a while now, engraved upon a bow in order to remember it. Well here you\'re then :\nForgetfulness of Magic arrow : 4 Flexible Woods, 5 Rings of Mental State, 10 Bows of Pure Crystal, 1 Water.\nI hope this helps.";
D.q[6322] = "I just got some bad news and I\'m really not in the mood to hear any more. If you have some encouraging information, speak up, otherwise, get out of here before I tear you limb from limb.";
D.q[2676] = "Don\'t come back if you don\'t have what I asked you - a Pandapils!";
D.q[8019] = "So, I really have lost everything. I\'m counting on our mayor to inflict a suitable punishment.";
D.q[2065] = "Like I tell you! Besides, she foresaw you coming here. But, like any other good initiate, you should create your first tie with her. To do so, nature is willing to sacrifice some of her goods, but you\'ll have to protect it in return. Go and see the lumberjack : he certainly has what you need, a branch of Hurrywood, and come back to me after you saw him.";
D.q[6342] = "And who else exactly do you want me to work for? Aren\'t we in Bonta after all? You should think twice before asking such idiotic questions.";
D.q[2528] = "Are you here for a libation to the goddess?";
D.q[4352] = "Any news of that merchant?";
D.q[5402] = "Come on now, sing with me. \'Bibi bibi bibi Bibiblop. On the Rocky Plains. You\'re the king of the Blops. Bibi bibi bibi Bibiblop. Your love. Solid as a rock\' \nDon\'t you want to sing with me? You just want to get into the dungeon? Okay, give me the key and I\'ll let you in.";
D.q[6691] = "";
D.q[1099] = "Hm, their cannons are not too bad, they\'re made in a workshop near here.\nThe only problem is that Amayiro only likes knives so the heavy stuff is often left in the warehouse during battles...";
D.q[7355] = "";
D.q[4929] = "I will not fail to mention your more-than-effective participation to Amayiro and the other Order Masters.\nf you have nothing else to do, go back to Amayiro. He\'s not short of missions and he always needs help from someone.";
D.q[4096] = "Out of my sight, traitor!";
D.q[488] = "I\'ve sent one of my disciples, Yrun Teullair, to steal the manual of the Tailor of Amakna. Unfortunately, he didn\'t come back. I\'m afraid he might have decided to keep it for himself. \nIf you bring the intact manual back to me, you\'ll be fairly rewarded.";
D.q[6818] = "An owl spelling \'Scram\'? What in the name of the great Enutrof are you talking about? Stop talking nonsense and go bet on the outcome of the next fight.";
D.q[6692] = "";
D.q[4054] = "What an insult! I\'m the greatest dressmaker in Bonta. The most important people hire my nimble fingers to make them the best outfits ever stitched together.";
D.q[2405] = "Are you sure you really want to become a Shoemaker?";
D.q[1917] = "Pnj(471) et Message(1909)";
D.q[6220] = "Xephires? Ah but of course, Xephires! I often made beautiful costumes for him out of pure Shin Larva silk and Moon fabric. Now there\'s a man who\'s got taste and who likes luxury. Unlike some people I can think of. Was there something else?";
D.q[2917] = "I hope you\'re bringing me good news, young spy #1!\nWhat can I do for you?";
D.q[2383] = "Are you sure you want to start a career as a Dagger smith?";
D.q[6694] = "";
D.q[3147] = "I hope you\'re proud of yourself! You stepped on my boomerang and now it doesn\'t work properly. It doesn\'t fly into my hands anymore, it shoots straight for my opponents! It\'s unbearable! You\'re nothing but a dirty Piwi killer, an Arachnee-batterer, a Dragoturkey beheader!";
D.q[6693] = "";
D.q[8020] = "You need to know that to enter the wreck and fight the rebellious spirit, I\'ll have to turn you into a pirate ghost. If you go alone, you\'ll have no chance of winning. Find yourself some companions but bear in mind that only 4 of you will be able to fight.";
D.q[1858] = "I wouldn\'t mind a little help actually. We need a lot more Gobbly wool for our stock. If by any chance you could go shear some beasts...";
D.q[6695] = "";
D.q[831] = "I heard this morning that it\'s possible to communicate with the dead when you\'re a spirit.\nI want you to kill yourself, find my father\'s body in the Brakmar cemetery, and ask him where he hid his will. I\'ve been looking for it for years!\nHis grave is in the centre of the cemetery. There should still be a big bunch of flowers on it...";
D.q[2378] = "Are you sure you want to start a new career as a Staff Sculptor?";
D.q[8021] = "My soul is freed, but I\'ve decided to stay here, as it\'s much more fun.\nMy loot is located to the south of the Cradle of Alma, in a chest. The wood is damaged, you\'ll have no trouble breaking it if you hit it.";
D.q[2379] = "Are you sure you want to start a new career as a Wand Sculptor?";
D.q[1552] = "Your collabouration with Bonta. People want this! They want you. This is your chance!";
D.q[2450] = "This is where we lock up Amakna\'s worst criminals. If you ever capture one, bring them to me.";
D.q[6697] = "";
D.q[6696] = "";
D.q[7354] = "";
D.q[8022] = "I can\'t turn you into a pirate ghost while you\'re seasick.";
D.q[6698] = "";
D.q[2387] = "Are you sure? This job is quite hard and requires a lot of time and money.";
D.q[1547] = "Your craving for adventure will inexorably lead you to hidden treasures, but also to certain death...";
D.q[8023] = "Is he taking the mickey?\nSo tell me, my dear tourist, it was a question of finding my father\'s loot, and not just a stupid letter. You\'re just like Count Harebourg, you promise to help us and ultimately, you abandon us.";
D.q[6154] = "So what about those souls I asked you for?";
D.q[3157] = "And do you know why I\'m the best? Obviously you don\'t. You\'re way too stupid #1, you don\'t know a thing, so let me explain it to you.\nI\'m the best because I built the best ship on the continent. It\'s more beautiful that all the flower fields of Rosal, it can resist Rushu\'s flames, and it\'s faster than a featherless Tofu falling out of a tree. I discovered the Minotoror Island with this ship a long time ago.";
D.q[2996] = "Are you trying to fool me? I wrote that one. You probably found it in a library! Go back there and take a copy of the Dragon Era!";
D.q[6699] = "What a sordid place, I hope not to languish here too long.";
D.q[4894] = "Hello, so Amayiro sent you.\nI have a problem - the Hammer of Light was stolen by the Brakmarians and the spirit that lived inside it was destroyed. I don\'t have a clue how to make a hammer like that, so I need your help. I asked Amayiro, but he wasn\'t able to find out either.";
D.q[3931] = "See... I told you that I\'d be rewarded for my talent! Even the King asks me to do stuff for him!";
D.q[716] = "I can assure you, you won\'t regret remaining faithful to me. I\'ll put you to the test again. How about a little training with Torche, the militiaman. When he saw his brother Tarche\'s new teeth, I pointed out you were the one in charge of extracting them... that was the right thing to do, wasn\'t it? ";
D.q[4821] = "";
D.q[7283] = "";
D.q[3203] = "By the look on your face, you didn\'t understand a word of what I just said. Fortunately, you\'ve got a map there - use it to find your way around, and organise things with your teammates. Yeah, teammates. I forgot to tell you that you won\'t make it if you\'re alone. The more of you there are, the more likely you are to make it through this terrible labyrinth. Once you\'re inside, you\'ll see that each door and each switch has a colour code.";
D.q[4073] = "I can see you\'re starting to regret all this... It\'s about time!\nHowever, I won\'t forgive you that easily. You\'ll have to be useful at least once in your life.";
D.q[4131] = "I know that island. It\'s infested with pirates and Kokokos. I\'m not afraid of Kokokos. I was brought up among a primitive Kokoko tribe when I was young and believe me, those creatures are even more stupid than Iops! However, beware of pirates, they are deceitful, vile, wicked and filthy, their breath is more putrid than a blocked Bherb cloaca. Basically, we must repair my ship as quickly as possible. \nI\'ll need wood, which you should be able to find on this island. You must also find Flib\'s Cursed Chest. It\'s a living chest that I abandoned here. It contains the necessary tools to fix the ship\'s sail.";
D.q[6171] = "You\'re not as stupid as you look, are you. Would you be interested in joining the ranks of the defenders of Bonta? If so, I can offer you a purse full of Kamas and teach you a few veteran tricks that\'ll be of great use in a fight. \nSo, what do you say?";
D.q[6242] = "I\'ve known Xephires for a few years and I can tell you that I probably wouldn\'t be as famous as I\'ve been since I won the Amakna\'s Got Talent contest. All the same, he doesn\'t seem to like you, which is why I\'m going to have to ask you to stop bothering us.";
D.q[6579] = "I came with thirty years of tough practice behind me, I found some travelling companions who wanted to steal Chafer bones. Everything was going fine until the Eniripsa and the Feca abandoned us, saying that their mother wanted them back home. Seriously though... can you believe it? Leaving us there in a dungeon to fend for ourselves? My other companions tried to get out, but they were slain and chopped up into little square pieces. As for me, I dug a hole with my spade and make a ladder with the leftovers of my travelling companions. I\'m lucky that none of the monsters from above have ventured down here yet. So how about we get out of here together?";
D.q[6415] = "By the Twelve, how is that possible? You...you\'re poor! With your odd, country bumpkin appearance I had a few doubts, I\'ve to admit. Reassure me, it\'s not contagious, is it? Here, take this recipe and go away, I don\'t want to catch it.";
D.q[5615] = "By the look of you, you had a rough time with that Enutrof. Go and get some rest, Knight of Hope, I\'m going to get to know our guest a little better. \nAs for the Brakmarians at Terra Bitya\'s tomb, I\'ll speak to Ebru Of El about them. Maybe his spies discovered something I haven\'t.";
D.q[7351] = "";
D.q[348] = "I need an amulet carved from wood to build up my collection. If my memory serves me right, Agrid the Lumberjack is wearing one around his neck, maybe he would agree to exchange it for some help. \nBring me back this amulet and I\'ll exchange it for a useful parchment. \n\nIf you like adventure, I advise you to meet the Dreggon breeder near the deserted village. He\'s offering a generous reward.";
D.q[6397] = "Ah yes, I heard you were going to come by and deliver these documents. Don\'t worry, as long as I have them, the Brakmarians won\'t be able to lay their hands on them.\nSay hello to Amayiro for me, will you?";
D.q[1852] = "What should I do? My cellar is infested with Mimice! The noise is horrible and the stench is just awful. What\'s worse is it attracts every Bow Meow for miles around! It\'s scaring my dear TwitTwit! And when my TwitTwit is scared, it makes me very angry!";
D.q[4663] = "So you miserable sod, you want me to take you to Brakmar, eh? It\'s not a town for the faint-hearted, you know. It was built on a former battleground, the walls are still wet with the blood of our foes, the moats full of Rushu\'s anger and me... well, I decapitate any inexperienced adventurers who disrespect the city or my Dragoturkey... they say my beautiful beast doesn\'t suit me... what do they know?\nOkay, well, do you want a ride on my mount to the Brakmar Zaap? Well, you\'ll have to stroke him a bit first, let him get used to you.";
D.q[4022] = "Let me think about it, okay?";
D.q[2611] = "As you may already know, the Xelor\'s Divine Clock is set according to the pulsation of the Dofus. The heartbeat of each Dofus occurs at the very same moment... If you listen carefully, you might hear a light throbbing... So? No? Well... maybe next time! Anyway, I\'m going to tell you what you should have discovered on your own. The harmony of our World relies on this heartbeat!\nBut more and more explorers are moving heaven and earth to find the dragons\' eggs.... All this mess is not good for the Dofus! I can feel they\'re getting restless... It\'s as if they\'re being disturbed and affecting the Divine Clock in turn! And if time can\'t be stabilised, the temporal portal will be thrown open...";
D.q[2815] = "As you may know, if you\'ve read the book of Myamowa Musashwan, Pandawas are equally comfortable with all the elements. It\'s up to you to find your own way amongst the four!";
D.q[4546] = "Well done, you got the patrol. Here\'s your bonus. Unfortunately that\'s the end of the good news. The Brakmarians found out about Nara\'s traps and since he refused to work for them, they got rid of him. He fought hard for his life, and took several brakmarians off to the grave with him. We still don\'t know what the Brakmarians are planning to do next.";
D.q[7280] = "I\'ve to go to the marketplace and I can\'t let people use the forge in my absence. You\'re going to have to leave.";
D.q[720] = "Well, #1, you\'ve been brave until now. I\'ve got a perilous mission for you. Go explore Brakmar but don\'t get caught.\nLook closely at the mechanism of their city door. Any piece of information will be useful. Don\'t come back unless you found something interesting.";
D.q[3869] = "As\'Ruoy\'Dnim was putting Amakna under his implacable yoke and letting his diabolical armies plunder and pillage. The demons were extremely powerful and everyone was too afraid to do a thing... But Allister had companions, and above all, he had a plan. Through sly trickery, he managed to lock As\'Ruoy\'Dnim up in a jail. Unfortunately, as I was saying, the rogues helped him to escape.";
D.q[6608] = "Hello. I was waiting for you. I think enough time has passed.\nWhile you were out bravely fighting the Brakmarians, I sent other militiamen to find out about this Bwork Mage. The Sadidas weren\'t too talkative, but Touh Flowa, Sadadi Sama\'s disciple in Astrub, made an exception to the rule, without telling too many people. Continue the investigation from there, and good luck. Jiva is watching.";
D.q[4511] = "Ah, bravo! Some supplies? We\'ll sort out taking him some.";
D.q[2641] = "Poochan very happy. Poochan give you secret to use source with no side effect.";
D.q[2711] = "I\'m forging a shield for the Pandasiman... He\'s a Master in the art of shield fighting. He only uses shields blessed by me and his shield was stolen by Pandikazes.";
D.q[6524] = "That\'s beginners luck, well, that or the devil\'s luck, and I\'m tempted to say the latter. I\'ll reply to your question, that way I\'ll leave here tonight still with a few Kamas in my pockets. Do you know where the Miners\' Market it? Yes, the one in Brakmar, obviously! Petra\'s hideout is near there, that\'s all I can tell you, and I don\'t want to talk to you anymore.\nDon\'t forget your winnings.";
D.q[6303] = "I see. So in the end, you don\'t know a whole lot about the place...\nThe Well of the Corrupted Souls is a place where wandering should blocked in our world gather to become servants of evil. The wells are a link between our world and another plane of existence where corruption is the accepted way to do business. That\'s why these wandering should, once trapped in the wells, never come back the same as they went in... and that\'s when they do come back at all.";
D.q[5767] = "I can\'t think for the life of my why that Ronan the Jocker fellow is more talked about than you. It\'ll cost you 4,000 Kamas to go neutral.\nAnd don\'t forget, you can join the weaker alignment for free!";
D.q[6522] = "That\'s beginners luck, well, that or the devil\'s luck, and I\'m tempted to say the latter. I\'ll reply to your question, that way I\'ll leave here tonight with a few Kamas in my pockets. Do you know where the Miners\' Market is? Yes, the one in Brakmar, obviously! Petra\'s hideout is near there, that\'s all I can tell you, and I don\'t want to talk to you anymore.\nDon\'t forget your winnings.";
D.q[2177] = "Dear #1... You know that we, the Srams, can invoke a double of ourselves. And right now, you\'re talking to my double. Ahha! I\'ll be glad to explain it all if we ever meet each other around Brakmar. But for now, I\'ve a mission to entrust you with!";
D.q[4753] = "What? You gave the burglars a thumping and then you managed to convince them in their hideout to come and join the militia? Excellent Brakmarian reflexes! Never forget that the more deceitful people are, the more likely they\'re to be useful to us eventually.";
D.q[4885] = "Amayiro needs me? It\'ll be a pleasure to help him, of course. Tell him I just need a day\'s notice so I can close the shop and let my customers know.";
D.q[4423] = "What? We had more men than them, we were more powerful and you still managed to lose!? Imbecile!\nWell, what\'s important is the fact that we now know the Bonta militia is under-equipped. The moment to attack has come. \nBut... before that I want to find out what Kaffra Keeper thinks about all this. If you don\'t know him already, you can usually find him in the Tower of Orders in Brakmar.";
D.q[6298] = "Impatience? I love that. Ok, since you\'re so eager, here\'s my plan - Xephires is in a position to give us information on Bontarian convoys. We\'re going to attack these convoys, but sending Brakmarians there will only arouse suspicion. What\'s more, I never had much faith in my officers to bring back the whole of the loot, so I\'ve got a great plan that should deflect suspicion and ensure that I get the booty... all of it! It\'ll just appear in my mens\' pockets as if by magic.";
D.q[3899] = "So, are you going to help us or not?";
D.q[937] = "Welcome to the Kikim Inn, what can I do for you ?";
D.q[4404] = "It\'s a pity you didn\'t come sooner, I could have let you know before you returned to Bonta. \nBrakmar is up to something... something against our city, but I still don\'t know what it is. What I do know is that a lot of thieves who are mixed up in the affair have gone to join Oto Mustam. Their hideout is near the Handyman\'s Workshop and you often find Ze Krow hanging around there too. They seem to be well organised, so if you\'re going to pay them a visit make sure you find some Bontarians to go along with you.";
D.q[1440] = "Hemm! Amayiro wants more evidences...take this confession, it will be more convincing...\nOtherwise I don\'t know... you can ask Ture Inge how to lead an investigation, he may have some suggestions...";
D.q[289] = "I\'m selling this land for next to nothing! If you buy the land, I\'ll throw in the house for free. You\'ll see, it\'s a really ni... really nic... really n...well, it\'s actually an awful place to live. I\'m sick of it, but I don\'t have got enough money to buy myself a new place.";
D.q[4050] = "Hello noble Sire!";
D.q[4598] = "A good choice. Here\'s the reward for your loyalty. Tell Amayiro that the spy was being helped by several Brakmarians when you found him and you weren\'t able to stand up to so many enemies.";
D.q[6241] = "I remember you. You came before to ask about him. What I can tell you is that he loves precious metals, diamonds and rubies, but he especially has a weak spot for exotic objects.";
D.q[985] = "Oh, a visitow to my fowest, you awe vewy bwave to ventuwe hewe.\nI\'ve a favow to ask you, I\'m too old to go to Wabbit Island by myself, but I\'d like to continue my weseawch into that wace.";
D.q[3156] = "Hello #1. I\'m Nikos. Nikos Monot. I\'m the greatest sailor of all time. I\'ve seen places no other eye has seen, I\'ve gazed beyond the oceans and I\'ve penetrated the giant mystery of the Kralove. As Tina Burner used to say... I\'m simply the best.";
D.q[1110] = "Pleased to meet you. My name is Fulsura. The Aphrodite of Brakmar, Queen of Beauty. What do you want? If you come here for you-know-what, you can forget about it. First of all, you\'re very ugly. Second of all, you would never be able to afford it.";
D.q[5679] = "Recently, a courageous member of the Order of the Valiant Heart delivered the old Enutrof Terra Cogita to us. He\'s currently in Bagrutte\'s Inn and holds vital information on the location of Statuettes of Sumen, and we need this information.\nThe renegades we interrogated revealed the existence of these statuettes that are a symbol of mankind\'s good and evil. Maimane gave them to Sumens and Brakmar seeks to seize them, so we must act quickly.";
D.q[6208] = "You know darling, discretion is one of the most important parts of my job. I really can\'t tell you anything about all this, but I know some people who can.";
D.q[6231] = "I was just admiring the rolling countryside from my Imp Carrier when I fell off... I leant too far over the edge. Fortunately a goblin broke my fall. There was nothing left of him but a stinking pile of mush. Then the goblins captured me, but they had too much to carry so they got rid of the Sram they had with them - must have found me more palatable - and, well, you know the rest. As far as I could see they were planning on preparing a feast and I was the main course!";
D.q[3765] = "Excellent work. I\'m proud of you!";
D.q[4616] = "Excellent work. The Iop needed to dig to find the Fogornleg Horn, and fortunately for us he didn\'t realise that. Bring it closer to me, please. It\'s truly a magnificent Horn, it must contain incredible magic powers. It will be the ace up our sleeves in the fight against Brakmar.";
D.q[6172] = "Excellent, you\'ve made the right decision!\nGo quickly to Oto Mustam in the Brakmarian Militia and tell him I sent you. There\'s a shortcut to get to the dark city, I\'ve drawn it on your map for you. \nActually, don\'t tell anyone else about this little favour as Astrubian militiamen aren\'t allowed to recruit on behalf of the big cities. It\'s our little secret, OK?";
D.q[1252] = "Thanks to your information, 10 of your colleagues managed to carry out a particularly destructive raid on Brakmar. Tomorrow, they\'re invited to the ceremony where they\'ll be given medals. While I think of it... They\'ll probably be exhausted after such a mission and won\'t have time to get new clean cloaks. Would you mind taking care of it?";
D.q[664] = "Since the quadramental breeze blew on our world, many things have changed. We are gradually beginning to learn how to control this celestial power. Soon we will completely master it, and then!... But let\'s talk about what brings you here...";
D.q[2277] = "And yesss! I\'m never wrong! Rhahahahaha! I can recognize a brave warrior from fifty yards! Do you remember when we waged war from Sidimote to Bonta, marched to Wabbit Island and returned to Brakmar? That cost me nine toes...! If we had used the Zaaps instead of footing it, it would have been a lot easier, huh?!";
D.q[1206] = "Leave me alone with my grief... He left, you understand? Left!";
D.q[2743] = "Avoid the damned springs. Did you know our goddess only had one single hangover in her whole life, but that it\'s been lasting for a thousand years? Well, her divine binge made her as sick as a dog, which created the little springs of magic water that flow just round the corner from here in Terrdala and Akwadala. Be careful! This water can imprison the souls of people who fall into it, and trap them in a deadly curse... it\'s probably the smell that does it. The unlucky victim then takes on the appearance of the last imprisoned soul...";
D.q[4523] = "What\'s yellow, bubbly and is guaranteed to transform any old weasel into a valiant knight? My quality guaranteed beer, that\'s what! (This is not a guarantee.)";
D.q[6525] = "That\'s beginners luck, well, that or the devil\'s luck, and I\'m tempted to say the latter. I\'ll reply to your question, that way I\'ll leave here tonight still with a few Kamas in my pockets. Do you know where the Miners\' Market it? Yes, the one in Brakmar, obviously! Petra\'s hideout is near there, that\'s all I can tell you, and I don\'t want to talk to you anymore.\nDon\'t forget your winnings.";
D.q[2983] = "You don\'t know it yet but it\'s your dearest wish.";
D.q[733] = "Brakmar defeated us yesterday. They used a summons we\'ve never seen before.\nI\'d like you to go and ask Zeurg, the Osamodas Master, about this creature. He always gives good advice.";
D.q[4668] = "According to a recent report, we\'re still one step ahead of the Bontarians. Get yourself over to Moon Island and convince Elturt to reveal the location of the Fogornleg Horn, in exchange for the Spentox Back-Scratcher.\nHmmm. Try offering him some Salad laced with pollen, it should calm his mistrust somewhat. We need to keep luck on our side. I\'m sending the other militiamen to watch the Bontarians, so don\'t count on them to help you with this mission.";
D.q[6356] = "I know that traffickers are operating in this port, I\'d bet on your mother\'s life! Ever since Wabbit and Moon Islands were discovered and the tourist trails have been put in place by the \'A\' Tourist Team, illegal activity has flourished. Speaking of illegal, you look pretty dodgy to me yourself. You wouldn\'t be a diversion by any chance, would you?";
D.q[1575] = "So I\'ll be the next steward... How sad for our dear Tedeor though...\nBy the way, tell me young disciple, could you do me another favour?";
D.q[2190] = "I don\'t know what\'s happening but more and more adventurers come to this city every day. It\'s getting really stuffy round here.";
D.q[1512] = "Not long ago, Brakmar and Bonta suddenly resurfaced. Whim of gods or of protectors, no one knows yet. Amakneans who lapsed into dark cults migrated to Brakmar and, on the contrary, those of light migrated to Bonta. The new inhabitants of Brakmar elected 3 representatives, one for each major dark cult: Djaul, Hecate and Brumaire to rule the city. I\'m the representative of Brumaire.";
D.q[3163] = "I\'m sure you\'d like to know what lies on top of the mountain behind these steps. Well it\'s simple, I trapped the biggest Crackler I ever managed to catch there and he can\'t get back down now as he\'s put on quite a bit of weight. He\'s huge, monstrous, terrifying even! He\'s so dangerous that I\'ve blocked access to the steps. If you have a key on you, I\'ll let you go past, and you\'ll see that I wasn\'t lying, and you\'ll probably be scared, so you\'ll cry like a little girl, begging me, Krunchie the Crackler hunter, to help you!";
D.q[5682] = "You\'re kidding me, aren\'t you? I just told you that I don\'t do anything for anyone any more.\nUgh, stop making that face, I\'ll help you - but it\'s the last time, understood?\nHowever, you\'ll need to fetch the ingredients. I need 5 Potions of Old Age, 10 Magical Cure, 3 Edelweiss, 10 Flax Seed, 1 Sunflower Seed and 1 Quetsnakiatl Feather. Think you can manage that?";
D.q[4543] = "I think it\'s time to test the fruits of our labour. The militia is on manoeuvres and we\'ve just received a few cases of equipment from Nara. I want to plan an ambush on the Brakmarian patrol but to do that, I need to know where and when to strike. You\'re going to visit our spy in Brakmar and ask where to find reports on the rounds of the Brakmarian patrols. As soon as you have these documents, come and report to me. We\'ll have to strike quickly, before the Brakmarians realise the documents have been stolen and they change their plans.";
